{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"87853cae-be89-4bb6-ab26-7048de405eed","content":"Here's what you need to do:\n\n1. **Update package references** in your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Remove -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.visualstudio\" Version=\"...\" />\n\n   <!-- Add -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3.runner.mtp\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n   ```\n\n2. **Note:** This requires migrating from **xUnit v2 to v3**, since MTP support is only available in xUnit v3. Key changes:\n   - Replace `xunit` (v2) with `xunit.v3` package\n   - Update `using Xunit;` — most APIs are compatible but some attributes/assertions changed\n   - `[Fact]`, `[Theory]`, `[InlineData]` remain the same\n   - `Assert` API is largely the same with minor additions\n\n3. **Add an MTP entry point** — xUnit v3 with `xunit.v3.runner.mtp` auto-generates one, but ensure your project has:\n   ```xml\n   <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n   ```\n\n4. **Run tests** with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test          # still works\n   dotnet run           # also works directly (MTP is in-process)\n   ```\n\n5. **Optional:** Add `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` to your `.csproj` to enable full `dotnet test` integration with MTP.\n\nWould you like help automating the migration on a specific project?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d72ee3e0-fc7e-47b0-8245-9417572494e7","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration path.","outputTokens":447,"requestId":"340D:9F564:58CC81A:60D821F:69F3FA01"},"id":"0a590d38-106a-4c86-9af3-719136fcfdeb","timestamp":"2026-05-01T00:55:39.214Z","parentId":"c635c453-8e2c-43c9-8163-08c1d5845b6f"}
